ITppptool Help

PPPtool is a graphical interface for connecting to remote networks
via dialup modem.

The Main window consists of a Menu, a display of active account 
information, the 'Connect/Disconnect' Button, some mock 
'status lights', and a 'status' line.

Menu Items
The Menu bar contains four menus:
1. 'File'
2. 'Edit',
3. 'Accounts'
4. 'Help'.

The 'File' menu contains three items:
1. Save Accounts
2. View Log
3. Exit

The 'Edit' menu contains two items:
1. Manage Accounts
2. Edit Preferences

The 'Accounts' menu is a dynamic menu and holds the names of all accounts
which have been created.

The 'Help' menu contains two items:
1. 'About PPP Tool'
2. 'PPP Tool Help'


Using ITppptool

I. Creating Accounts
To create a new account, Select 'Edit/Manage Accounts'
Click on 'New'. A window will appear with the following fields:
( ** denotes a required field )
[ ** Account Name ]: Enter the name of the account
[ ** User ID ]: Enter the login name or ID of the account
[ Password ]: Enter the password of the account ( if one exists )
[ ** Phone Number ]: Enter the Phone Number of the account
[ DNS Domain Name ]: Enter the domain name of the account ( if one exists )
[ DNS Search Domains ]: Enter any domains which DNS should search
[ Account Nameserver #1 ]: Enter a primary nameserver for the account
[ Account Nameserver #2 ]: Enter a secondary nameserver for the account
Near the bottom of the window are the following checkbuttons:
[ ** Authentication Type ]: Select the authentication protocol or method
[ Default Route ]: If selected, adds a 'default route' option to pppd
[ Create /etc/resolv.conf ]: If selected, copies the DNS information to /etc/resolv.conf
II.   Saving Accounts
To save the current account information to the account file,
select File/Save Accounts. If there have been any changes to
the accounts, a prompt will pop up to confirm the save.
Clicking 'Yes' will save the account data, clicking 'Cancel' will
not save the account data and return to PPP tool.
 
III.  Editing Accounts
To make changes to an account, first select Edit/Manage Accounts.
Click on an account name in the window, then click on 'Edit'
A window will appear with the account information.
Edit any fields or select/deselect any items, then click on 'Save Edits'
The window will close and the changes will be saved in the currently
running program, but will NOT be save to the accounts file.
To save the changes to the accounts file, select 'File/Save Accounts' and
click on the 'OK' button
.
IV.  Deleting Accounts
To delete and account, first select Edit/Manage Accounts.
Click on an account name in the window, then click on 'Delete'
The account will be deleted in the currently running program, but will
NOT be saved to the accounts file.  To save the changes to the accounts
file, select 'File/Save Accounts' and click on the 'OK' button
.
V.    Making an Account Active
To make an account active means to make it available for connecting.
There are two ways to do this:
1. Select the account from the 'Accounts' menu item in the main window.
2. In the 'Account Manager' window, select the account and click the
'Make Active' button.
VI.   Preferences
Upon first starting ppptool, a set of default preferences will be loaded.
To make sure the correct settings are in effect, check the preferences
window by selecting 'Edit/Edit Preferences'.
The settings in the preferences are:
Modem Port (required):  This is the port to which the modem is connected.
Flow Control:  hardware, software, or none.
Port Speed (required)
Init String: Enter any modem initialization string here.
Connect String: Reserved for future use
PPP options: Reserved for future use

VII.  Connecting with PPPtool
To initiate a connection, follow these steps:
1. Select an account and make it active ( See V. above )
2. Make sure your modem is connected to the correct port, and that
the correct cable is connected between the modem and the computer.
3. Verify the account information is correct, then click on the 'Connect' Button.
4. If possible, turn up the volume on the modem so that you can hear it going
off-hook, dialing, and connecting.
5. Monitor the 'Status' line at the bottom of the main window, and the log
window as well ( File/View Log ).
VIII. Exiting PPPtool
To exit PPPtool, select 'File/Exit'. If there is any account information
which has not been save to the account file, a dialog will pop up asking
whether to save, cancel, or return to PPPtool. Clicking 'Yes' will save
the account settings to the file. Clicking 'No' will exit PPPtool without
saving the account changes, and clicking 'Cancel' will return to PPPtool
without saving any changes to the accounts file.
